title: Skydiver crashes hard into water off the coast of Florida
text:
A skydiver came in too strong for a landing and lost control upon impact off Florida's East Coast.

It only took seconds to change the course for the adventure-seeker near the city of Sebastian.

Video posted to Jukinmedia.com on September 26 shows the 10-second clip of the man falling normally before his parachute flips over.

It was a bad skydiving session for this man, who lost control upon impact off Sebastian, Florida

The man hit the water with too much speed causing a loud thud

He was hurled back in the air after the initial impact off Sebastian, Florida

He slammed hard into the water at speed causing a loud thud.

He is then hurled at least 50 feet into the air. There is no word on the man's identity or if he suffered any injuries.

The circle represents where a skydiver ended his adventure after a crash landing in Florida
description: A skydiver came in too strong for a landing and lost control upon impact off Florida's East Coast. The video was filmed in Sebastian, Florida.
